<h2>//SOLO</h2>
<p>I started playing the violin at the age of 5 and have given numerous solo recitals.  I made my "orchestral" debut at the age of 8, playing the Bach Double Violin Concerto with my teacher at the time.  Since then, I've performed with various orchestras playing the works of Paganini, Prokofiev, and Tchaikovsky.  I don't play as much solo repertoire today, but who knows what the future holds...I miss the thrill of being on stage!</p>

<h2>//CHAMBER</h2>
<p>I started seriously playing in chamber music groups in college where I played in a cello quintet, piano quartet, and string quartet.  Since graduation, I've primarily played in a piano trio.</p>

